The paper focuses on integrating heterogeneous data sources for software analytics, which is a key aspect of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also proposes an ontology-based approach for data integration, which is a common technique in database research (cs.DB). The paper discusses the use of real-time analytics, which can be achieved through machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of static code analysis, which is a topic in programming languages research (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the automation of the data integration process, which can involve techniques from machine learning and data mining (cs.LG).
